Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.69,0:03:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daru?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.40,0:03:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No record in the outbox...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.66,0:03:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But as for the inbox, \Nthe D-mail arrived five days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.70,0:03:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.03,0:03:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the past change?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.45,0:03:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.30,0:04:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We sent a D-mail to Daru five days in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.51,0:04:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}telling him the position of the cards,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.34,0:04:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so he could win the Feyris Cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.05,0:04:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushii?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.51,0:04:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Question for you... In the Feyris Cup last week...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.43,0:04:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? I lost? Immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Thanks. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.57,0:04:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daru's message didn't alter the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.87,0:04:32.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the way the game went, \Nit should have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't enough to change world lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we need an easier way to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.25,0:04:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if the past has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It still isn't like I agree with \Nthese experiments, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.89,0:04:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So... What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.43,0:04:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About you being the only one to remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.48,0:04:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.52,0:04:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the power of the magic eye, Reading Steiner!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.27,0:05:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to see if that's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have you send the next D-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.57,0:05:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.52,0:05:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worried about a time paradox?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.49,0:05:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels unfair to change the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.08,0:05:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've only lived eighteen years, \Nbut I don't want to change any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.81,0:05:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all part of my life, even the failures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you love experiments, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is that wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.10,0:05:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you'll just sit back and watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.27,0:05:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as others sacrifice themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.56,0:05:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A true mad scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.98,0:05:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:05:50.66,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2\fs33\frx12\fr14\pos(640,258)\c&HE5E5E5&}Please
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:05:50.66,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2\frx2\fr13\fs33\pos(460,451)\c&HCBCBCB&}I want to send a D-mail too{\c&H4435BC&}!\N{\c&HCBCBCB&}Moeka
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But seriously... \NIf we're going to perfect the D-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.62,0:05:57.83,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3\fs39\frx12\fr14\pos(591,244)}Please{\c&H8067C3&}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.62,0:05:57.83,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be2\frx2\fr15\fs39\pos(437,551)\c&HC1C1C1&}It's okay, right{\c&H4C24BA&}? \N{\c&HC1C1C1&}Please{\c&H3A1BB0&}! \N{\c&HC1C1C1&}Moeka
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we'll have to continue our experiments...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:04.55,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be4\fs49\frx12\fr14\pos(555,166)}I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:04.55,CellphoneR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be3\frx2\fr13\fs44\pos(386,416)\c&HC1C1C1&}A lab member, too, right{\c&H4F2AB7&}? \N{\c&HC1C1C1&}Moeka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:03.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiryuu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.35,0:06:19.02,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,She overwhelmed us...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:25.32,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.03,0:06:27.28,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Those crêpes were good...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.28,0:06:28.19,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:32.16,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You look bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.16,0:06:34.12,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm waiting for someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.70,0:06:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't scare Nae!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.66,0:06:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.69,0:06:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Nae.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's leave this loser alone and go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.67,0:06:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayuri-oneechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:06:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.72,0:07:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's one for Okarin, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.40,0:07:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.97,0:07:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Suzu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.65,0:07:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the part-timer girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... What happened after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.41,0:07:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.29,0:07:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you ask John Titor?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.00,0:07:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I don't know if \Nwhat he says is accurate...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.25,0:07:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which part?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.46,0:07:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.42,0:07:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a Titor otaku, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.39,0:07:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More sparks between you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.36,0:07:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's her problem, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:07:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting makes me sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.54,0:08:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.54,0:08:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.95,0:08:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No private messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.79,0:08:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We want something simple, that will make it clear
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whether the past's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.26,0:08:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I changed my cell phone four days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I want to tell myself not to do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.52,0:08:23.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.81,0:08:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if the past changes, \Nyou'll have a different cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.60,0:08:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.19,0:08:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let us begin the experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Activate the Phone Microwave \N(name subject to change)!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.67,0:08:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so round...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.75,0:08:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.01,0:08:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used the wrong number for \Nthe Lotto-6 you asked me about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:08:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.09,0:09:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good... Good to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.31,0:09:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The day nears, when your heart's eye will open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.98,0:09:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.95,0:09:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.36,0:09:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.58,0:09:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.11,0:09:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wear Mayushii's cosplay sometime soon, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.62,0:09:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really into that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.37,0:09:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you won't?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.91,0:09:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you'd look great...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.61,0:09:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.79,0:09:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.88,0:09:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good kid, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.22,0:09:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.91,0:10:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This feeling again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The past changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Where's Shining Finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.26,0:10:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.25,0:10:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese... Do you speak it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.51,0:10:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rukako didn't stop by?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.28,0:10:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rukako? Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.41,0:10:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Moeka... Where's Moeka?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moeka-san? Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.96,0:10:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiryuu Moeka!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.33,0:10:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:10:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.26,0:11:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kiryuu Moeka... I've never heard that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.32,0:11:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another D-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.77,0:11:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The past changed, \Nand Moeka's very existence disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.65,0:11:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.98,0:11:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Up to July 31st, my inbox still has messages from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.46,0:11:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Something wrong?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Sorry, I'm kind of busy."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll message you later."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.51,0:11:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the past altered in such a way that, \Never since four days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when she received that message,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.43,0:11:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this Kiryuu... Moeka-san
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.19,0:11:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,changed her actions and never came to the lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.85,0:11:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.44,0:12:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this time, only you remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.61,0:12:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Reading Steiner, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, just saying that embarrasses me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.78,0:12:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you should call it that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.83,0:12:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in your personal opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.62,0:12:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power to maintain memories across world lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.42,0:12:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it real?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.01,0:12:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll talk tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.89,0:12:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you tomorrow, Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.52,0:12:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I really do have that ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.35,0:12:40.11,Cellphone,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(480,480)\q2\be3\fs150\fr5\c&HC6C0BF&\move(480,140,-880,140)}I want you to be the messiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.69,0:12:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.74,0:12:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed they can sleep at the lab...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said it's 'cause he's a mad scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.62,0:12:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! Let's all sleep over at the lab!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:12:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the guys aren't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.33,0:13:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, why not come to my hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.25,0:13:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.54,0:13:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.67,0:13:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.72,0:13:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll come over soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.85,0:13:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruka-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.85,0:13:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.02,0:13:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.94,0:13:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't bring the Magic Blade Samidare?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.61,0:13:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.99,0:13:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that, Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, Ruka-kun is my guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to wear my cosplay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.03,0:13:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's transform, Ruka-kun. Transform!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.00,0:13:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I mean, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.38,0:13:43.92,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take off your clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.92,0:13:45.96,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,No, don't touch me there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.67,0:13:47.55,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:49.01,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put it on myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.01,0:13:50.43,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,So leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:53.31,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to know the trick to putting this on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:56.43,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please... Don't take off my clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.43,0:13:59.10,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,This is very yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.10,0:14:02.27,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Rukako is a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.27,0:14:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.36,0:14:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's even better!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.82,0:14:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kirari-chan from Rai-Net.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're as cute as I imagined, Ruka-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.79,0:14:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is really embarrassing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.34,0:14:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.75,0:14:26.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cute is justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.97,0:14:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to get a low-angle shot of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Okarin?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.39,0:14:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.25,0:14:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.18,0:14:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've just been victimized by a \Nfierce psychological attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.98,0:14:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.02,0:14:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My soul... My soul is being devoured!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.11,0:14:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's wrong, Kyouma-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.08,0:15:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop staring, pervert assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.60,0:15:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not staring!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Further win!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.27,0:15:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of this cosplay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it look good?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.92,0:15:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... It's very cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Cute... Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.80,0:15:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try on the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.06,0:15:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came here because I had a request for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't come here to wear my cosplay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.23,0:15:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I said no. But you wouldn't listen to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.23,0:15:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I was just really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.16,0:15:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what did you want to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.30,0:15:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.08,0:15:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to let me send a message to the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came by...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to apologize for having missed\Nthe Lotto-6 yesterday. And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.17,0:15:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Another D-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.09,0:15:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wh-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.80,0:16:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The past changed, and Moeka's very existence disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.10,0:16:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.62,0:16:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for listening when I shouldn't have!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.61,0:16:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.24,0:16:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruka-kun, what kind of message \Ndo you want to send to the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.43,0:16:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.05,0:16:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be a girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:28.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like the way I look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'd feel better about myself \Nif I could be a girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always felt that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.50,0:16:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is she saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.72,0:16:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assistant, you appear to have \Nmade a fatal mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.65,0:16:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.19,0:16:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rukako is no girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.26,0:16:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.23,0:16:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of joke is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.53,0:16:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't believe me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.90,0:16:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you call yourself a scientist, \Nthen see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.45,0:17:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a cute girl couldn't be a guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.83,0:17:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.35,0:17:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to be a girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.64,0:17:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know if sending a D-mail
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.73,0:17:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be enough to change your gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.63,0:17:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard of something...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That if you eat lots of meat \Nwhen a baby is in your tummy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll have a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.70,0:17:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With a lot of vegetables, you'll have a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.62,0:17:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to send a D-mail, telling your mom
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.16,0:17:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to eat lots of vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.75,0:17:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.62,0:17:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall grant your wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:54.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.21,0:17:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good for you, Ruka-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.26,0:17:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.26,0:18:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't changing someone's gender a bad idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.34,0:18:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it's possible to affect it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.22,0:18:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just by eating vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.47,0:18:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.56,0:18:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no scientific evidence for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.93,0:18:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must have really been worried about it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if that makes him feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.53,0:18:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rukako, from now on, you're Lab Member 006!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.19,0:18:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.36,0:18:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us begin the experiment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you're seventeen this year, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.53,0:18:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.12,0:18:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you were born in 1993...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.80,0:18:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did cell phones become popular in Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it was around 1996.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.26,0:18:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they may only later have \Ngotten messaging capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.06,0:18:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, when Urushibara-san was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.77,0:18:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a good chance his mom \Ndidn't own a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can't send the D-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We could change it, so it sends sinister microwaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.40,0:19:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have enough sinister microwaves for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.49,0:19:03.91,Default-alt,,0000,0000,0000,,Good... Insult me more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.25,0:19:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terrified by my own talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.21,0:19:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not this again...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,479)}If she doesn't have a cell phone, \Nsend it to her pager!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.80,0:19:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pagers...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.05,0:19:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A system using EM waves to \Ntransmit messages to small receivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.88,0:19:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the 1990s, \Nthey enjoyed enormous popularity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The emergence of cellular phones \Nrendered them obsolete.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.42,0:19:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pagers?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.44,0:19:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're very knowledgeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.48,0:19:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you were a Cel-Pager, not a Cel-7?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's written right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.77,0:19:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not read it yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.57,0:19:43.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lab Member 006, Urushibara Ruka!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.57,0:19:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for your first mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find out if your mother had a pager.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.53,0:19:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And get that number!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.16,0:19:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.55,0:19:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom had a pager!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:19:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the number.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:19:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You thought of what to write, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.00,0:20:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Eat vegetables for a healthy child."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.55,0:20:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you can only send eighteen hiragana...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.24,0:20:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can only send numbers to a pager.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.93,0:20:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Transform these to numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.85,0:20:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.19,0:20:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need two digits for voiced consonants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.27,0:20:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.29,0:20:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can send a total of thirty-six English letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.36,0:20:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That message puts you four characters over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.66,0:20:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.49,0:20:31.37,Channel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be4\fs23\fr-5\pos(243,420)\c&H554E42&}Eat veggies for a healthy child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we turn this into numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.38,0:20:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, starting it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.33,0:20:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.28,0:20:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.34,0:20:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.74,0:21:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My Reading Steiner activated!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.16,0:21:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.28,0:21:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Some people are like that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.12,0:21:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruka-chan, I think you'd look great \Nin something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.37,0:21:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.05,0:21:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.59,0:21:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.88,0:21:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you staring?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.93,0:21:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.18,0:21:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's difficult to ask if Rukako became a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.02,0:21:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.02,0:21:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.79,0:21:46.44,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of perverted thing are you imagining?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.44,0:21:48.03,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez, Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:52.33,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take my eyes off you two perverts for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.33,0:21:55.45,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a pervert! I'm a perverted gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.45,0:21:58.12,Default - margin,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter... It really doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.17,0:22:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.04,0:22:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The world line changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.88,0:22:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Something happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.05,0:22:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But what?

